media_camera Fire crews outside Miller Technology High School. Picture: Melvyn Knipe Liverpool Students evacuated after fire at Miller Technology High School Cindy Ngo, Liverpool Leader February 21, 2017 12:27pm
Up to 650 students have been evacuated from a school in Miller after a fire broke out in a woodwork room this morning.
Emergency services were called to Miller Technology High School on Cabramatta Ave shortly before 11.30am, following reports a fire had broken out in a dust extraction unit.
Firefighters from six surrounding stations took just 15 minutes to bring the fire under control and another hour to put it out due to smouldering saw dust in a hopper.
The fire is believed to have caused smoke damage.
A Fire and Rescue NSW spokesman said there had been no reports of injuries.
It is not yet known when students can return to classrooms.
